[Patient] How much water should I drink each day to manage my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for 8-10 cups of fluid daily, including water, herbal tea, and low-sodium broth.
[Patient] Can I drink other beverages like soda or juice?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit sugary drinks and opt for water, herbal tea, or unsweetened juice to manage fluid intake.
[Patient] How do I know if I am drinking too much fluid?
[Healthcare Educator] Watch for weight gain, swelling in your legs, and shortness of breath as signs of fluid overload.
[Patient] What should I do if I notice these symptoms?
[Healthcare Educator] Contact your healthcare provider immediately if you experience these symptoms to prevent complications.